>[Question]
>What is the probability of rolling 5 dice (1 roll per die) one time 
>and having the first roll be a 1, the second a 2, the third a 3, the 
>fourth a 4, and the 5th a 5?  I.e. the results of a player's first 
>attempt during his/her turn of a game of Yahtzee.
>What is the probability of performing this feat twice in a lifetime?
>
>[Difficulty]
>I did this feat in December 2003 and thought that it was a pretty 
>rare event.  Two weeks later, I did it again.  I calculated the 
>probability to be 1 in a 10-billions answer (can't remember the 
>number exactly).  Probability was always a strongpoint for me, but 
>I'm really terrible with math overall.  Just want the correct answer 
>to end my curiosity.  
